ce:section.ce:para:
The optical absorption spectra were employed to investigate the effect of CQDs on the light harvesting ability of the obtained materials. The optical absorption edge of pure Bi4O5I2 was about 520nm (Fig. 6
                     ), which limits the materials cannot make full use of solar light. After the CQDs were modified on the Bi4O5I2, the absorption edges of CQDs/Bi4O5I2 materials widened to 650nm and the absorption intensity enhanced gradually with the increase of the amount of CQDs when compared with Bi4O5I2, which could be attributed to the photon absorbing ability of CQDs. This interesting finding indicated that the introduction of CQDs could enhance light harvesting capability of the materials and produce more effective electrons and holes to participate in the photocatalytic activity under visible light irradiation. Fig. 7
